                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_325-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="en" key="work_9469">A manuscript of bayad form mostly containing poetry with other assorted notes.</title>
                     <note>Much of the MS is taken up by a long devotional and ethical poem in mutaqarib metre, missing the beginning. Other pieces are of a similar pious nature. Ruled margins and dividing panels. A few headings in red. Some folios tinted blue.</note>
                     <incipit>Ankih amad nuh falak mi'raj-i u</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For Price's bequest see J.R.A.S., iii (1836), pp. xii-xiv, lx.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
